The paper deals with the capacity of channels, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The channels considered are finite state machine channels, which are a type of discrete system (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the limitations of algorithms in approximating the capacity, which is a topic in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with the concept of information stability, which is a topic in systems and control theory (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the construction of a subfamily of channels, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC).
